<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One important way for activist short selling t=
o work is that a short seller makes a big bet against a company=E2=80=99s s=
tock, the short seller publishes a report saying that the company is a frau=
d, the company publishes a rebuttal saying that actually it is good and the=
 short seller is the fraud, and then some outside=C2=A0referee with some of=
ficial power evaluates both reports and decides who wins.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not an absolute requirement: The short=
 seller might publish a report saying =E2=80=9Cthis company=E2=80=99s sales=
 growth is not going to be what the market expects, so it is overpriced,=E2=
=80=9D and the company could publish a response saying =E2=80=9Cno,=E2=80=
=9D and then some combination of (1) the company=E2=80=99s future performan=
ce and (2) the reactions of other investors will decide who wins. Here,=C2=
=A0there is no outside referee and no single definitive determination of wh=
o is right and who is wrong.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But if you are going to bother with activist s=
hort selling, you mostly aren=E2=80=99t putting out noisy reports about gro=
wth and valuation doubts. You are mostly putting out noisy reports about fr=
aud or crime or =E2=80=9Cthe entire product is fake.=E2=80=9D And if you ar=
e noisy enough, some responsible regulator will look into your report, and =
the regulator will either (1) decide that the company is a fraud and bring =
charges, in which case its stock probably crashes and you win, (2) decide t=
hat=C2=A0you=C2=A0are baselessly slandering the company and bring charges a=
gainst=C2=A0<em>you</em>, in which case you lose, or (3) close the case wit=
hout action, in which case the stock probably recovers and you probably mos=
tly lose. An activist short report is often an indirect request for <em>reg=
ulatory action</em>, and it succeeds if there=E2=80=99s an enforcement acti=
on and fails otherwise.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; =
background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a></p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"></=
ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last month Hindenburg Research <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly9oaW5kZ=
W5idXJncmVzZWFyY2guY29tL2FkYW5pLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB25e6e4b6" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">put out a report</a> accusing India=E2=80=99s Adani Group of being =E2=80=
=9Cthe largest con in corporate history.=E2=80=9D (Adani <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucHJu=
ZXdzd2lyZS5jb20vbmV3cy1yZWxlYXNlcy9hZGFuaS1ncm91cC1oaXRzLWJhY2std2l0aC1kZXR=
haWxlZC1yZXNwb25zZXMtdG8taGluZGVuYnVyZ3MtdW5zdWJzdGFudGlhdGVkLWFjY3VzYXRpb2=
5zLTMwMTczNTgwNC5odG1s/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB207d7474" itemprop=3D"Story=
Link" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; te=
xt-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-col=
or: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> put out<=
/a> a <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264=
446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYWRhbmkuY29tLy0vbWVkaWEvUHJvamVjdC9BZGFuaS9JbnZldHNvcnM=
vQWRhbmktUmVzcG9uc2UtdG8tSGluZGVuYnVyZy1KYW51YXJ5LTI5LTIwMjMucGRmP2xhPWVu/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB34fb550c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> rebuttal</a> calling Hindenburg =
=E2=80=9Cthe Madoffs of Manhattan,=E2=80=9D Hindenburg put out <a href=3D"h=
ttps://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly9oaW=
5kZW5idXJncmVzZWFyY2guY29tL2FkYW5pLXJlc3BvbnNlLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc=
87f4d03" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> a reply to the reply</a>, etc.) Adani is a network of lar=
ge infrastructure companies that are publicly traded in India and that are =
controlled by Gautam Adani. The infrastructure is not fake =E2=80=94=C2=A0A=
dani really builds stuff and makes money =E2=80=94=C2=A0and Hindenburg does=
 not claim that it is. Instead, Hindenburg=E2=80=99s essential claims are:<=
/p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The prices of Adani Group stocks sure=
 seem high? (=E2=80=9CEven before examining the evidence put forward in thi=
s report and based solely on financials taken directly from its companies, =
the Adani Group appears to be highly overvalued.=E2=80=9D)</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A lot of the public shareholders of the Adani Grou=
p companies seem to be offshore shell companies that are secretly affiliate=
d with and perhaps controlled by Adani, and that might be manipulating the =
stock. Under Indian rules, listed companies need to have a free float of at=
 least 25% of their shares, that is, at least 25% of the shares have to be =
in the hands of outside investors. Hindenburg alleges that a lot of the out=
side public investors in Adani companies are actually controlled by Adani.=
=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The Adani companies are <a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvYmE0ZjQyNDktYzQ0NS00MzY5LWE4ZmItZTdiMGIwYzEz=
MDU1/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc89d5980" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> highly leveraged</a>, and =
(says Hindenburg) =E2=80=9Cintricately and distinctly linked and dependent =
upon one another. =E2=80=A6 We believe it could take only one serious liqui=
dity event at a single entity to trigger a negative cascade of events at ot=
her group entities which could affect the entire Adani Group.=E2=80=9D</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Adani denies these claims. The Hindenburg repo=
rt is very long and miscellaneous (=E2=80=9CGautam Adani=E2=80=99s Brother-=
In-Law, Samir Vora, Was Allegedly A Ringleader Of The Same Diamond Trading =
Scam,=E2=80=9D ah!) and frankly I am not sure what the payoff is supposed t=
o be. But if you put those three claims together and assume that they are t=
rue, then you could imagine them pointing in a direction something like: =
=E2=80=9CAdani Group might be a bunch of real companies with fine businesse=
s, but their stock prices are way too high because they are manipulated by =
insiders trying to pump up their valuation by making heavily levered trades=
 on a deceptively small float, and when that is discovered the stock prices=
 will collapse.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-2" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important;=
 background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Adani Group stocks fell a lot after the Hi=
ndenburg report =E2=80=94=C2=A0wiping out <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloo=
mbergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9=
uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDkvYWRhbmktc2hhcmUtcHJpY2UtY29sbGFwc2Utd2lsbC=
1yZXZlcmJlcmF0ZS1pbi1pbmRpYT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMjA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVka=
XVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBh=
aWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6c627327" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> more than $=
100 billion of market value</a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0and Adani had to delay <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDQvaW5zaWRlLXRoZS=
0xOS1ob3VyLW1lbHRkb3duLXRoYXQtanVua2VkLWFkYW5pLXMtc2hhcmUtc2FsZT9jbXBpZD1CQ=
kQwMjA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRl=
ciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB1450c5f4" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">  stock</a> and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZ=
XdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDQvYWRhbmktZmxhZ3NoaXAtc2hlbHZlcy0xMjItbWlsbGlv=
bi1ib25kLXBsYW4tYWZ0ZXItbWFya2V0LXJvdXQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIwOTIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkY=
mdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjA5Jn=
V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5bc9cf2d" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
  bond</a> offerings, though more recently the stocks have recovered somewh=
at. None of that =E2=80=A6=C2=A0none of that is an=C2=A0<em>answer</em>, th=
ough, you know? Are Adani=E2=80=99s outside investors real, or are they Ada=
ni affiliates? The stock price action doesn=E2=80=99t tell you that.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In theory the referee here might be the Securi=
ties and Exchange Board of India: Hindenburg is accusing Adani of violating=
 its=C2=A0listing requirements, and Adani is denying those claims. But in p=
ractice there is another set of referees: the index providers. Index provid=
ers are mostly not in the business of deciding questions like =E2=80=9Cis t=
his company overvalued=E2=80=9D or even =E2=80=9Cis this company a fraud,=
=E2=80=9D but they=C2=A0<em>are=C2=A0</em>in the business of deciding quest=
ions like =E2=80=9Chow much of this company=E2=80=99s stock is held by insi=
ders,=E2=80=9D just because many indexes are weighted by free float. (The i=
dea is that, if an index fund has to buy X% of every company, it should hav=
e to buy X% of the=C2=A0<em>available </em>shares of each company, not the =
ones that don=E2=80=99t publicly trade.)=C2=A0If Adani says that 25% of its=
 shares are publicly held, and Hindenburg says that really the number is mu=
ch less than that, then that is a factual dispute that the index providers =
can, and sort of has to, referee.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So the <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvODhlN=
DY4ZmQtYmUwOC00ZmRkLWJhNWEtZjY0ZjA2ZjJiZjI4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8fca2a=
b1" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> Financial Times reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Global index provider MSCI is set to change it=
s weightings for Adani Group stocks after reviewing how many shares can be =
freely traded, in a further setback for the Indian conglomerate reeling fro=
m fraud allegations.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">MSCI said =E2=80=9Ccertain investors=E2=80=9D =
in Adani Group =E2=80=9Cshould no longer be designated as free float pursua=
nt to our methodology=E2=80=9D after receiving feedback from =E2=80=9Ca ran=
ge of market participants=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Any cuts to the determined free float for the =
Adani Group=E2=80=99s listings would result in smaller weightings for those=
 stocks in MSCI=E2=80=99s closely watched indices, triggering outflows as i=
nvestors who track the benchmarks reduce their shareholdings. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Shares in Adani Group=E2=80=99s listed compani=
es sold off following the announcement, with flagship business Adani Enterp=
rises falling as much as 15 per cent after posting gains for two straight d=
ays.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An Asia equity strategist at one Wall Street i=
nvestment bank said MSCI was likely to follow the precedent set by previous=
 reviews of different companies and cut its free float estimates by around =
half.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CPotentially the weight of Adani stock=
s in the indices will be cut in half as a result, and passive investors wil=
l have to sell to reduce [the stocks=E2=80=99] weight accordingly in their =
portfolios,=E2=80=9D the strategist said, adding that the bank estimated th=
is would result in about $1bn to $1.5bn of outflows.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">MSCI is an important referee of this dispute i=
n two senses. One, there are some international investors who own the stock=
s in MSCI indexes in proportion to their index weightings, and they will ju=
st mechanically sell Adani stocks if MSCI cuts their weightings. Two, MSCI =
is a more-or-less neutral arbiter that will=C2=A0<em>decide the factual que=
stion=C2=A0</em>of whether Adani=E2=80=99s free float is actually free floa=
t. If it cuts Adani=E2=80=99s weighting, that suggests that Hindenburg=E2=
=80=99s claims are more likely to be true; if it maintains the weighting th=
en that suggests they aren=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, MSCI is not the sort of ref=
eree that can make a definitive decision. If a short seller can get a regul=
ator to shut down trading in a company=E2=80=99s stock for fraud, that=E2=
=80=99s a pretty definitive win: The stock price will collapse and the shor=
t seller will make money. If Hindenburg can get MSCI to lower Adani=E2=80=
=99s index weights due to a revised free-float calculation, that is a techn=
ical win, but I am not sure it=E2=80=99s a death blow.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I said that there are two ways for activist sh=
ort selling to work, either (1) appealing to a referee or (2) generally try=
ing to convince the market of your skepticism about the business. There is =
maybe a third approach that is somewhere in between those two, which is con=
vincing=C2=A0<em>creditors=C2=A0</em>of a business that does a lot of short=
-term borrowing to=C2=A0<em>pull their credit</em>. This is a markets-orien=
ted approach, appealing to investors rather than to some regulator or other=
 outside arbiter. But it can also be fast and definitive: A company that re=
lies on short-term borrowing can be crippled pretty quickly if that borrowi=
ng dries up.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-=
color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0If Hindenburg is right about Adani, you=E2=80=99d expect (1) Adan=
i=E2=80=99s=C2=A0<em>lenders=C2=A0</em>to demand their money back and (2) A=
dani not to have it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sort of mixed results on that one. <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDgvYWRhbmktcGxhbnMtdG8t=
cHJlcGF5LTUwMC1taWxsaW9uLW1hcmNoLWxvYW4tdG8tYmFua2luZy1ncm91cD9jbXBpZD1CQkQ=
wMjA5MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlci=
Z1dG1fdGVybT0yMzAyMDkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cBfec8c1e7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">  Bloomberg reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Adani Group plans to prepay a $500 million=
 bridge loan due next month after some banks balked at refinancing the debt=
 following a short seller report that sent the group=E2=80=99s assets tumbl=
ing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Barclays Plc, Standard Chartered Plc and Deuts=
che Bank AG are among banks that lent Adani $4.5 billion to finance the pur=
chase of Holcim Ltd. cement assets last year. A portion of that loan is due=
 March 9.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lenders were in talks to refinance the loa=
n up to a week before the critical report from Hindenburg Research was publ=
ished, according to people familiar with the matter. Those negotiations sta=
lled after the report alleging fraud led to a massive selloff, chilling the=
 banks=E2=80=99 willingness to refinance, the people said, asking not to be=
 identified discussing a private matter.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The development is the first concrete sign tha=
t global banks are becoming more wary of financing Adani=E2=80=99s empire a=
nd coincides with comments from France=E2=80=99s TotalEnergies SE that a mu=
lti-billion dollar plan to produce green hydrogen with the Indian tycoon ha=
s been put on hold, pending audits of his conglomerate.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloom=
bergbusiness.com/click/30506312.264446/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQv=
YjVhZDE4NTItZGQwOS00YjM4LThkNzQtYzJhOTk0NjIzOTVm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBc=
712f010" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> the FT again</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Gautam Adani, whose Indian business empire is =
under pressure over fraud allegations, repaid a $1.1bn share-backed loan la=
st week after facing a margin call of more than $500mn, according to four p=
eople with direct knowledge of the matter. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lenders of the $1.1bn loan, which included=
 Barclays, Citigroup and Deutsche Bank, requested last week that the billio=
naire top up the amount of stock pledged against the loan after a sharp fal=
l in the shares of the listed Adani companies, according to the people with=
 knowledge of the matter. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As the shares continued to slide, Barclays inf=
ormed Adani of a margin call equivalent to 50 per cent of the loan in cash,=
 said the people, who spoke on condition of anonymity.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Rather than post cash against the loan, which =
did not mature until September 2024, the Adani Group=E2=80=99s founder and =
his family opted to repay it completely. Adani has not disclosed the source=
 of the funds used to repay the loan.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Adani Group said it did not receive a formal r=
equest for a margin call. The full loan was repaid early =E2=80=9Cper our p=
repayment planning=E2=80=9D, the company added.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The banks demanding their money back scores a =
point for Hindenburg, but Adani paying it scores a point for Adani.</p>
