ts.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, though, the mechanics of the deal seem t=
o rely on Hudson Bay converting its preferred stock into common shares and =
reselling them=C2=A0in the open market, presumably to retail investors, pre=
sumably at prices that are =E2=80=A6=C2=A0you know, determined by the marke=
t, but maybe not prices that Bed Bath=E2=80=99s board and advisers think ar=
e rational right this minute. Bed Bath was already looking for bids for its=
 assets in bankruptcy and not really finding any, suggesting that the value=
 of its equity, to sophisticated investors, was rather less than zero. And =
the structure of the Hudson Bay deal itself suggests that=C2=A0<em>Hudson B=
ay=C2=A0</em>doesn=E2=80=99t think Bed Bath=E2=80=99s stock is worth its ma=
rket price: Hudson Bay gets to buy stock from Bed Bath over time at hefty d=
iscounts to whatever the market price is, so it=E2=80=99s not exactly makin=
g a big bet on Bed Bath=E2=80=99s long-term value. =E2=80=9CWe believe that=
 recent volatility and our current market prices reflect market and trading=
