</a>=C2=A0That=E2=80=99s not that much? For this much new stock? It=E2=80=
=99s not like Bed Bath issued, or Hudson Bay sold, $1 billion of stock all =
at once in the last day or two. But even announcing a <em>plan=C2=A0</em>to=
 issue many times the market capitalization of the company is a big deal; t=
he fact that the stock is still trading higher than it was two weeks ago se=
ems like a win. This deal is enormously=C2=A0<em>dilutive</em>, but it=E2=
=80=99s probably (a bit?) better for the stock than=C2=A0<em>bankruptcy</em=
>, and the stock price reflects that.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Elsewhere in Bed Bath,=C2=A0Ben Fife at Chicag=
